President Donald J. Trump is hosting an Opioid Summit at the White House to discuss the Administration's efforts to combat the opioid crisis. The President has made it clear that his Administration will fight back against this crisis. The Administration is focusing on education and prevention, as well as providing more treatment and recovery options for those struggling with opioid addiction. Federal law enforcement under President Trump has also been working to curb the illegal importation and distribution of opioids that has contributed to the epidemic.